    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-08-24T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-08-24T20:00:00-05:00" n="357"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760C.62/1088c: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="49" xml:id="d357fn49">The same, with the omission of the
                        last paragraph, on the same date, to the Embassies in France (No. 647),
                        Germany (No. 376), and Poland (No. 40), and at 11 p.m. to the Embassy in the
                        United Kingdom (No. 691).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-24T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 24, 1939—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>78. The President has just sent the following messages to the Chancellor of the
                    German Reich and to the President of Poland. [Here follow the complete texts of
                    the messages under reference, printed <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.] These
                    messages will be released to the press at 10 p.m. Washington time.</p>
                <p>You should convey these texts without delay to the Foreign Office, stating in
                    writing that you are doing so by instructions of the President, who regards
                    these two messages as supplementary to his message to the King of Italy,<note
                        n="50" xml:id="d357fn50">See telegram No. 77, August 23, 11 a.m., to the
                        Ambassador in Italy, <ref target="#pg_351">p. 351</ref>.</note> and has the
                    hope that the latter may find them helpful should he decide that he could make a
                    move for peace.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
